4}}</ref>\n*[[K. Kelappan]] \u2013 a.k.a. Kerala Gandhi, freedom fighter, founder of the [[Nair Service Society]]\n\n==Military personnel==\n*[[Maj Gen]] [[V.N. Parameswaran Pillai]] - General Officer Commanding (GOC), [[Travancore Nair Brigade]].\n* [[Lt General]] [[Kunhiraman Palat Candeth|K P Candeth]]<ref>BJP today, Volume 12. Page:20, Column:3</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CBK7DgAAQBAJ&pg=PT46&dq=K.P+Candeth+Nayar&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiI3bTZ5MriAhWI4HMBHcB4AxIQ6AEILjAB#v=onepage&q=K.P%20Candeth%20Nayar&f=false|title=Themes of Glory: Indian Artillery in War|last=Khullar|first=Darshan|date=2017-05-15|publisher=|year=|isbn=9789385563973|location=|pages=46|language=en}}</ref> \u2013 Lieutenant General in the Indian Army during Indo-Pak war\n*[[Sandeep Unnikrishnan]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8LjjDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT146&dq=Nair+caste+ashoka+chakra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjT18C1577bAhUD6Y8KHSCHBJgQ6AEIJjAA#v=onepage&q=Nair%20caste%20ashoka%20chakra&f=false|title=Ashoka Chakra Recipients|last=Aggarwal|first=Rashmi|date=101|publisher=Prabhat Prakashan|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Lakshmi Sahgal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/a-matriarchal-home-to-many-illustrious-daughters-of-india/989510/|title=A matriarchal home to many illustrious daughters of India - Indian Express|date=2012-08-17|website=Archive.indianexpress.com|accessdate=2016-02-24}}</ref> \u2013 freedom fighter of the Azad Hind Army\n* [[ Major General Jai Shanker Menon ]] \u2013 Head of Mission and Force Commander of United Nations Disengagement Observer Force\n* [[ Air Marshal Narayan Menon ]] \u2013 Air Officer-in-Charge (Personnel), Air Headquarters (1999\u20132004)\n*[[Neelakantan Jayachandran Nair|Colonel Neelakantan Jayachandran Nair]] \u2013One of the most decorated officer of the Indian Army, as the only serviceman to have been awarded both the highest ([[Ashoka Chakra (military decoration)|Ashoka Chakra]]) and second highest ([